User Profile

Personal Dashboard

You have successfully logged into the system and what you see now is your personal dashboard with your user name shown.

The dashboard displays system features and enables quick access to your recent records in the system, as follows:

  1. Cultural Objects displays recent cultural objects created or modified by you.
  2. Ongoing Activities displays recent activities that you participate in.
  3. Documents displays the most recent documents that you are involved with (as creator, author, co-author, etc.).
  4. Media
  5. System Help displays user guides on how to operate with system features.
  6. Saved Searches
  7. Recent Comments  displays recent comments that involve you.

While on your personal dashboard you can easily access:

  • All operations on your Projects, Cultural Objects, Documents and Folders, so you can start working immediately.

Back to Dashboard

You have opened the needed Project, Cultural Object, Document or Folder and now you want to return to your Dashboard. In order to do this you can choose between these two methods:

  1.  By pressing the Home icon
  2.  By using the Navigation Bar

 

Navigation Bar / Breadcrumb Section

The system shows a breadcrumb section, also called the Navigation Bar, which follows the sequence of objects from which you have your current object opened and not its hierarchical navigation. This bar is positioned right beneath the main menu.

User Profile Information

To access more detailed information related to your profile you can use the following tabs:

  1. Personal Dashboard  contains the users dashboard
  2. Cultural Objects  displays the Cultural Objects created or modified by you
  3. Documents  displays all Documents that you are involved in (as creator, author, co-author, etc.)
  4. Media  displays all Images, Audio, Video created or modified by you
  5. Activities  displays all Projects, Conservation Activities, Tasks that you are assigned to, participant of, supervisor of, etc.
  6. Exhibition displays all Exhibitions that you are involved in
  7. User Profile  contains detailed user information
  8. Permissions  displays all the permissions for users profile
  9. Versions  displays the previous versions of the user profile

Edit Your Personal Information

To edit your personal information select the Edit Action:

In Edit Mode you can add additional Personal Details, e.g. Department you are working in, Address, Telephone, etc.

Add Profile Image

Before you can add a Profile Image you need to upload the image in CS fist. To upload the image:

  1. Click on the Create / Upload and select the file and upload the image to the context of your user profile

    Note: You can upload the image to the context of a cultural object or to the context of project or any conservation activity. Uploading an image to the context of another system objects means that this image will be part of that context and the permissions on that image will depend on this context.
    Select the Upload option

     

  2.  The image Type will be preset if you are uploading png, jpg, tiff file types.
  3. Change the object name if necessary as the file name will be filled automatically
  4. Select Upload

Once the image is imported, select the Add Thumbnail action

If your profile already has a Profile Image, a Confirm message will be displayed. Press Yes to continue.

In the dialog:

  1. Enter search criteria to find the image you have uploaded. When the dialog opens, image is selected by default. However, you can narrow the search result by entering additional criteria for searching. 
  2. Select the image from the search result
  3. Press the Ok button

The image will be set as Profile Image.
